## EPIC-002 — Enhanced Markdown Preview with Interactive EPIC Rendering

**Phase:** 1
**Owner:** engineer
**Priority:** P0 — Foundation
**Estimated Effort:** 2 days

### Description

Replace the naive `MarkdownPreview.tsx` line-by-line renderer with a structured EPIC-aware preview that uses the parser from EPIC-001. Instead of rendering raw lines, it renders each EPIC as a collapsible card with interactive checklists, styled frontmatter badges, syntax-highlighted code blocks, and a visual dependency tag. Clicking a checkbox toggles it in the underlying markdown. The preview becomes the "Structured" view mode in the editor — a form-based editing surface layered on top of the markdown source.

### Context

The current `MarkdownPreview.tsx` (63 lines) only handles `#`, `##`, `###`, `- `, `* `, and plain text. It doesn't render:
